==English==

===Etymology===
From Hebrew אַחְאָב  (Ahab or Ach'av = "Brother of the father"), Standard Hebrew Aḥʼav, Tiberian Hebrew ʼAḥăʼāḇ, ʼAḫʼāḇ).

===Proper noun===
'''Achab'''

# A king of [[Israel]] according to the [[Bible]]
# A male [[given name]]

